#import "/formatting.typ": *

#show: recipe.with(
  title: "Sticky Rice",
)[
  - 1 cup short-grain white rice
  - 1 cup water
  - Salt, to taste

  Equipment:
  - Rice cooker#Fn.rice-cooker
  #v(0em)

  *Yields 2 servings.*
]


+ RINSE rice in cold water 4-5 times, or until water runs clear.
+ PLACE rice in pot.
+ FILL pot fully with cold water.
+ SOAK. #pause[30 min.]
+ STRAIN.
+ RESTORE rice to pot.
+ ADD water & salt.
+ POWER ON rice cooker. #pause[\~30 min.]

== Trivia

It frankly baffles me that this recipe works. It seems like rinsing the rice not just once
but effectively twice should get all the loose starches out, which I _believe_
#footnote[~Hang on, is this true?] is what makes sticky rice sticky. It does work though,
which I guess is pretty cool.

Oh, also, please do make more rice than prescribed. The more rice, the lower the chance of
burning, it seems.
